-- Deutsche Bank Said to Hire Chanik Park to Head South Korea Equity Research
-- Saeromi Shin
-- 2010-06-30T04:02:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/deutsche-bank-said-to-hire-chanik-park-to-head-south-korea-equity-research.html

          
          
             Deutsche Bank AG , Germany’s biggest
bank, hired  Chanik Park  from Morgan Stanley as head of South
Korean equity research, said a person at the bank with direct
knowledge of the matter.  
 Park, who runs Korea research at Morgan Stanley, will join
Deutsche Bank’s securities unit in Seoul on July 5, said the
person, who asked not be identified before a public announcement.  
 Park will leave Morgan Stanley in early July, said  Nick Footitt , a spokesman for the New York-based firm, in an e-mail.
Deutsche Bank declined to comment in an e-mail to Bloomberg News.  
 Park’s mobile-phone was switched off when contacted by
Bloomberg News.  
